Quote:  Here, you'll see the largest coprosma, kanono - with its broad green marbled leaves - a smaller, more slender version called karamu and a shrubby, pale green job which when crushed and held to the nose, will tell you in pungent terms how it earned the Latin moniker Coprosma foetidissma and it's common one of stinkweed.
